On Thu, 12 Dec 2002, Mike Visket wrote:

> Have 2 wheelchair (gel cell, 32 amp) batteries under the jump seat, running 
> in parallel (12 volt). From these I have an Aux lighter plug.
> 
> Good thing? Bad thing? So far (6 months with perhaps 20 chargings), so good. 
> The Aux batteries haven't exploded or anything yet.

Gel cell batteries are charged differently than regular batteries and need
a special charger to fully charge them, (however this charger will
overcharge your regular battery) so while you won't blow em up you also
won't get full service out of them and will probably shorten their lives

